      "writtenOn": "2016-11-03T17:19:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think what I would like to be able to do is to be able to state the depfile \u0027gen/skia.h.d\u0027 depends on find_headers.py, then the build would notice that find_headers.py is newer than the depfile, so the depfile is out of date and needs to be updated (so any target which needs it is out of date) so don\u0027t even look at the depfile.\n\nThis is the same behavior that the compiler wants as well, all the compiler generated depfiles should be considered out of date if the compiler itself changes.\n\nAll that being said it turns out that ninja no longer treats this situation as an error, it is now a warning and an invalid depfile treats the target as out of date. It seems the ninja on the bot is more than a year old and isn\u0027t the one in the current depot_tools. Well have to see why that is independently, but it appears this isn\u0027t an actual issue in the present.",
